<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5021] JavaStubCompilationUnit.addSource() should allow other extensions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5021</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed this while working on a replacement for GMaven.  I think JavaStubCompilationUnit should allow other extensions such as &quot;.gvy&quot;, &quot;.gy&quot;, &quot;.gsh&quot; to be used when adding sources.  This change in behavior was introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://fisheye.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy?cs=18020&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://fisheye.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy?cs=18020&lt;/a&gt;.  I think what we might want to do instead is blacklist &quot;.java&quot; rather than whitelist &quot;.groovy&quot;.  I&apos;ve attached a patch demonstrating this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12811713">GROOVY-5021</key>
            <summary>JavaStubCompilationUnit.addSource() should allow other extensions</summary>
